						<summary>

						<p>On a slab fixed into the bastion <hi rend="italic">(burz).</hi></p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1666 (expired) Rudhirōdgāri, Śrāvaṇa ba. 2, Wednesday,</hi> corresponding to 1743 A.D. July 27.</p>						

						<p>It mentions the construction of a bastion by Venkaṭadāsari, son of Koṇḍa-dāsari. The engraver of the inscription was Karumala Veṁggaya.</p>						

						</summary>
